G NORTH TOWARD THE HOPPERSTATION WITH 39 LOADED CARS OF COKE. THE 304 JOB WAS INSTRUCTED BY THE YARDMASTER TO COME OUT ON TRACK #100 AND THE 308 JOB HAD TO TRAVEL THE SAME TRACK TO GET TO THE HOPPER STATION TO DELIVER THE COKE. THERE IS A CURVE IN THE TRACK AT THE END OF ONE OF THE BUILDINGS IN THE AREA, AND AS EACH CREW TRAVELLED THE TRACK AND CAME AROUND THE CURVE, THEY SPOTTED ONE ANOTHER AND ATTEMPTED TO STOP, BUT WERE UNABLE TO DO SO AND COLLIDED, HEAD-ON. WHEN IT WAS REALIZED THEY WOULD COLLIDE, J. MEISTERICS, CONDUCTR ON JOB 304, JUMPEF FROM LOCOMOTIVE #960. HE RECEIVED SUPERIFICAL ABRASIONS TO HIS RIGHT KNEE,BOTH ARMS, AND LEFT AXILLARY AREA, AS WELL AS A CONTUSION TO HIS LEFT THUMB. HE WAS OFF WORK 22 DAYS. M. MCCAFFERTY, ENGINEER ON JOB 304, SUSTAINED A SUPERFICIAL ABRASION TO THE RIGHT POSTERIOR THORACIC REGION, AND HAD DISCOMFORT TO HIS NECK. HE MISSED NO WORK DUE TO THIS.NoneNoneNoneNone","Joint Track Type":"Industry","Joint Track Class":"1","Class Code":"3S","Class":"3S","Joint CD":"1","Incident Key":"CUVAC83999V198307","Report Key":"CUVAC83999V198307","Reporting Railroad Company Grouping":"","Reporting Railroad Class":"Class 3","Reporting Railroad SMT Grouping":"","Reporting Parent Railroad Company Code":"CUVA","Reporting Parent Railroad Company Name":"Cuyahoga Valley Rwy Co.","Reporting Railroad Holding Company":"Not Assigned","Other Railroad Company Grouping":"","Other Railroad Class":"","Other Railroad SMT Grouping":"","Other Parent Railroad Company Code":"","Other Parent Railroad Company Name":"","Other Railroad Holding Company":"","Maintenance Railroad Company Grouping":"","Maintenance Railroad Class":"Class 3","Maintenance Railroad SMT Grouping":"","Maintenance Parent Railroad Company Code":"CUVA","Maintenance Parent Railroad Company Name":"Cuyahoga Valley Rwy Co.","Maintenance Railroad Holding Company":"Not Assigned"}